reviewText: Excellent Messaging App But ... I have one problem with this app ... it does not have the ability to export an encrypted backup of my message database and identity keys. I would also like to see the ability to create encrypted backups on a remote filesystem, such as a CIFS or NFS Mount.

reviewText: Very Nice But... Would give 5 Stars but only if: (1) ALL recipients could receive encrypted texts and (2) if could send texts to more than 1 recipient per message and (3) could send more than 1 photo per message.

author: jennifer stock
reviewText: So far so good I've had no issues with this app. I mainly wanted to be able to send messages with hubby that wouldn't show in my regular messaging app. This does that and has functioned without a glitch!

author: Craig Grunenfelder
reviewText: Similar to stock Google messenger Like it for the most part. Seems to work well and layout is similar to the Stock Google messenger app. I don't like the extra steps to attach a photo however. That is annoying.

author: Colin Gauthier
reviewText: Works great for txting, not sure I like the phone part of it. People say I'm hard to understand on the phone through the app. Happy with all other aspects!

author: Serg Chernata
reviewText: Great messenger for the privacy minded

author: clint crosbie
reviewText: Great but no widget. I really like Signal. It is simple, clean, and functional. My only issue is that I would like for it to be my default message app but it doesn't have a widget. Could we please have one I the update?

reviewText: Excellent Excellent

reviewText: Generally very user friendly and convenient. Only issue is that sometimes it seems that recipients fail to be notified about a new message. That's the feedback I've had from friends in the USA.

reviewText: Beautiful application, love the minimal UI and especially the responsiveness of the app and handling of resource budgeting on lower end phones to optimize for responsiveness. I am a QA

reviewText: Dual sim support at last! Hats off you sobs! Been waiting to use this app again and now I can. Props to you scholarly gentlemen (and ladies?).

reviewText: Nice alternative nice price

author: Ansgar Fuchs
reviewText: Notifications don't work properly

author: Robert Stubenhofer
reviewText: Great messaging app Please fix pictured sent/received, the quality looks terrible.

author: Joby Titus
reviewText: Ok I can't speak to the security, but it doesn't let me take screenshots so people sending me msgs should feel secure. Doesn't work so well with apps when sharing things like links (from Spotify is the latest one I found)

author: Boodle Twain
reviewText: Group messaging is deplorable Group text seems like an afterthought in the app's design. Impossible to just add someone to a message... You have to go through a completely different set of steps to text more than one person. Why do you have to name the group when there is no way to see and select named groups later? Tapping the names at the top of the group thread ONLY SHOWS INFORMATION FOR THE FIRST GROUP MEMBER. No ability to compose first, then add recipients: you MUST enter all recipients before composing your message. This is a bug

author: John Lindner
reviewText: Huge issue, I have to uninstall Let me first start off saying I love this app, and would continue to use if anyone can troubleshoot this issue. When sending messages to other signal users, messages are delayed up to an hour and a half. Also, the read receipts are incorrect a lot of the time, I tested this. I have had many instances where I text my girlfriend and she doesn't get the message until 45 min later. While privacy and security are important, this problem can cause many issues in professional and personal setting. Please fix this.

author: Chuck Wells
reviewText: Great - but has a message delay bug This app is terrific except for one problem. I have the phone sitting there with Wi-Fi or mobile, strong signal, and volume up. I am expecting my wife to send something but I get nothing. I grab the phone to look, only to find there is no notification. I open the app and suddenly it goes "bing!" and shows me a new message, sent "18 minutes ago". I was here the whole time. What happened? This keeps randomly happening. When this happens, FB messenger is not having any issue. I dont think there is a net issue.

author: Justin Copeland
reviewText: Encryption has never been so easy Only issue is it's so smooth it makes me worry it's not actually encrypted

author: Patricia Hanser
reviewText: Ok Used to work well on my lg g2 but now on my lg g5, messages from other signal users do not come through until I click on the application and actually open it. Then they all come at once. Please update with a fix.

author: Mony Mony
reviewText: Signal Too many flaws, unable to open any media msgs sent to me, when I intend to send a pic, it tell me it isn't possible:(, can't access bimoji or audio recording. It has potential, i'll keep it just 'cause Edward Snowden recommended it during a conference, & 'cause I want ti support innovators who are worried about preserving our liberties. Try to fix it & let ne know how to fet updates, Thanks

reviewText: Sms good, mms won't send Mms grp msgs and mms pic msgs will not send while on 4G lte w/3bars of svc. Not had this issue in the past, just swapped from HTC 1 X to a S5 active.

reviewText: I really like this app but my contacts, who used Signal and then removed it, still show up as signal users. So my default is to send them an encrypted message, but they no longer have signal on their device so they dont get the message. Switching to unencrypted messaging for every message sucks. Fix this.

reviewText: Samsung galaxy s 1500 It's ok, have all these cool emoji but can't use 90% they don't show up on recipient phone? Attempted send pix that I took from the app & it failed ? blocking app needs more options like maybe the ability to read blocked msgs?

reviewText: Verification /doesn't work with Google voice numbers I downloaded this app and I had out in my Google voice number in. It sent me the message and the code but it didn't allow me to put in the verification code. It doesn't work with Google voice numbers.if you have a Google voice number don't try this app. Doesn't work with the gv numbers

reviewText: It's okay. 1. The app always opens in message list view even of you left it in a message itself. 2. Automatically switches from SMS to Signal message. 3. Search is not working.

reviewText: The application is light. It's a good alternative for Hangout. It is encrypted. The application need some serious improvement for SMS/MMS animated gif/large image. It's ridiculous that I can't send a regular gif through SMS/MMS but I can do it on any other messenger. PLEASE FIX THE MMS
